data.name: Lemon-Oregano Chicken Thighs with Feta and Spinach Stuffed Bell Peppers
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy lemon-oregano marinated chicken thighs paired with savory feta and spinach stuffed bell peppers, complemented by garlicky roasted broccoli for a delightful meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix lemon juice, oregano, salt, and black pepper. Marinate the chicken thighs for at least 30 minutes.
In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat. Sauté garlic until fragrant, then add spinach until wilted. Mix in the feta cheese and remove from heat.
Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds. Fill each pepper with the feta and spinach mixture.
Place the marinated chicken thighs in a baking dish. Arrange the stuffed peppers around the chicken and drizzle everything with olive oil.
Roast in the oven for about 25-30 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through and the peppers are tender.
On a separate baking sheet, toss broccoli florets with minced garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast in the oven for about 15-20 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Serve the lemon-oregano chicken thighs alongside the stuffed peppers and garlic roasted broccoli.
data.detailedName: Lemon-Oregano Chicken Thighs with Feta and Spinach Stuffed Bell Peppers and Garlic Roasted Broccoli
data.modifiersForBase: Marinated with lemon and oregano, served with stuffed bell peppers and broccoli.
